      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start but maybe a bit too generic. can you make it sound a little more personal? like, i want them to feel like we actually valued their specific contributions even though it didn't work out this time. maybe add a line about how much we enjoyed the technical deep dive session they did with our lead architect?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: We Miss Your Expertise\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you in good spirits. Your journey with us, although it didn't end as we may have hoped, was a memorable chapter in our story. The dedication you showcased during your impressive technical deep dive with our lead architect left a lasting impression on us, proving your mastery in system design.\n\nWe sincerely regret that we couldn't proceed with the hiring process for the senior developer role in Austin, given that the constraints of our project imposed a more specialized expertise in our cloud stack. While it's not the recognition we wanted you, your potential for growth and our belief in your capabilities embolden us to forward you for other possible matches.\n\nOn that note, we hope our paths might cross again, as we hold genuine interest in considering you for future opportunities. Thank you, from the bottom of our hearts, for the distinctive and a keen aptitude that both you and we have demonstrated.\n\nBest wishes,\n\n[Your Name]  \n[Your Position]  \n[Your Company Details]",
